      <relatedmaterial id="aspace_add-related">
         <head>Related Material</head>
         <p>Many Smith College faculty were involved with the workship award program, most notably Gertrude Parker Smith, and researchers are encouraged to consult the individual faculty files of committee members for potential information about the program. In addition, the College Archives has files containing biographical information on many of the alumnae who were awarded the workship. Often these files include correspondence, memorabilia, and photographs of their experience. Another source for information about the program may be the Office of the President files.</p>  
      </relatedmaterial>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_scope">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Southern Mountain Workship files contain correspondence, reports, newspaper clippings, press releases and photographs documenting the Southern Mountain Workship program which Smith College and the Conference of Southern Mountain Workers (CSMW) co-sponsored between 1944-1960.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
